#Text=UEFA Euro 2016 , days 6 and 7 :
#Text=four wins , two draws
#Text=Friday , June 17 , 2016
#Text=File photo of Dimitri Payet , the Man of the Match .
#Text=Image : Xavier NALTCHAYAN .
#Text=Yesterday , in UEFA Euro 2016 , England defeated their neighbours Wales 2 – 1 ; Northern Ireland won 2 – 0 against Ukraine ; and Germany and Poland had to settle for a goalless draw .
#Text=The day before , Russia lost 1 – 2 to Slovakia ; the match between Romania and Switzerland ended in a 1 – 1 draw ; and the hosts France won 2 – 0 against Albania .
#Text=Day six
#Text=Group B — Russia 1 – 2 Slovakia

#Text=After a draw in their opening match against England , Russia faced Slovakia on Wednesday , but Slovakia stunned the Russians as Vladimír Weiss and Marek Hamšík scored in the 32nd and 45th minutes respectively .
#Text=Denis Glushakov scored a goal for Russia .
#Text=The Slovaks won the match to leave Russia in last place in the Group B table .
#Text=Group A — Romania 1 – 1 Switzerland
#Text=Romania won a penalty kick in the 18th minute and Bogdan Stancu scored from the spot providing an early lead .
#Text=Admir Mehmedi scored an equaliser for the Swiss just before the one hour mark .
#Text=Both the teams had to settle for a draw .
#Text=Group A — France 2 – 0 Albania
#Text=The hosts France faced Albania in Marseille .
#Text=Though the French had greater ball possession , the match was goalless for 89 minutes .
#Text=Substitute Antoine Griezmann scored in the 90th minute , breaking the deadlock .
#Text=Dimitri Payet scored the second goal for Les Bleus in injury time .
#Text=France currently lead the table in Group A and will advance to the knock-out stage of the competition .
#Text=Payet was awarded Man of the Match for a second consecutive time .
#Text=Day seven
#Text=Group B — England 2 – 1 Wales
#Text=Welsh player Gareth Bale opened the scoring from a free kick in the 42nd minute as England took on Wales .
#Text=But their lead was nullified within a quarter of an hour as Jamie Vardy netted a goal .
#Text=The match looked likely to end in a draw , but then Daniel Sturridge scored a second goal for England to put them on top of the Group B table .
#Text=Bale has now scored twice in the tournament , both from free-kicks .
#Text=Group C — Ukraine 0 – 2
#Text=Northern Ireland
#Text=Ukraine dominated the game in terms of ball possession , but Gareth McAuley 's goal in the 49th minute gave Northern Ireland the lead .
#Text=Later , deep in injury time , Niall McGinn scored their second goal to ensure three points .
#Text=Three Northern Ireland and two Ukranian players were yellow-carded in the match .
#Text=Ukraine lost their previous match 2 – 0 against Germany and with just one match to come against Poland , they are at the bottom of the Group C table .
#Text=Group C — Germany 0 – 0 Poland

#Text=Polish captain Robert Lewandowski faced several of his Bayern Munich teammates , including Manuel Neuer , Thomas Müller , Jérôme Boateng and Mario Götze , in the Germany-Poland clash , but both sides had to settle for a goalless draw .
#Text=Six players were booked , three from each team .
#Text=Sami Khedira was the first to be booked , in the third minute .
#Text=Mesut Özil and Jérôme Boateng were also cautioned for Germany .
#Text=Krzysztof Mączyński , Kamil Grosicki and Sławomir Peszko were the three Poles to be yellow-carded .
#Text=Both teams won their previous game and both now have four points .
#Text=After the match , Germany manager Joachim Löw said , " All in all , a draw is a fair result , but I ’m not happy with it .
